import React, { useState } from 'react'; export default function ReportForm(){ const [form, setForm] = useState({ faculty: '', className: '', weekOfReporting: '', dateOfLecture: '', courseName: '', courseCode: '', lecturerName: '', actualPresent: '', totalRegistered: '', venue: '', scheduledTime: '', topicTaught: '', learningOutcomes: '', recommendations: '' }); const handleChange = e => setForm({...form, [e.target.name]: e.target.value}); const handleSubmit = async e => { e.preventDefault(); // POST to backend API try{ const res = await fetch('/api/reports', { method: 'POST', headers: {'Content-Type':'application/json'}, body: JSON.stringify(form) }); if(res.ok) alert('Report submitted successfully'); else alert('Submit failed'); }catch(err){ console.error(err); alert('Error submitting report'); } }; return (
); }
